		"description": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-5df00a56-7fff-3be3-c093-28978d847532\" dir=\"ltr\">Your life circumstances are truly exceptional; not only were you born with innate magical abilities, but you also have acquired an artifact, and through experimentation, you have begun to forging both into a unified whole. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\">Your Charisma or wielder spellcasting ability increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Your bonded artifact functions as a spellcasting focus for your sorcerer spells.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain proficiency with History or an expertise die if you are already proficient. You also gain the legends skill specialty, or a different History skill specialty if you already have it.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can spend a sorcery point and an artifact charge as a bonus action to empower your weapon. For the rest of your turn, the weapon deals additional force damage equal to your proficiency bonus and if you score a critical hit, you can recover an artifact charge or sorcery point (your choice). You can only recover a single point this way each turn, regardless of how many critical hits you score.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain the following minor metamagic option. It doesn&rsquo;t count against your metamagic options known: <strong>Wielded Spell</strong></li></ul>",
